              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5875398-rebecca?shelf=political">political</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5875398-rebecca?shelf=novellas">novellas</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5875398-rebecca?shelf=book-thing-free">book-thing-free</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5875398-rebecca?shelf=current-events">current-events</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3036034807" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3003107839245857364"><b>“Activism is not a journey to the corner store, it is a plunge into the unknown. The future is always dark.”</b> Solnit believes in the power of purposeful individuals working towards social justice, even in the face of dispiriting evidence (the largest protests the world had seen didn’t stop the Iraq War). Instead of perfectionism, she advises flexibility and resilience; things could be even worse had we not acted. At first I thought it depressing that 15 years on we’re still dealing with many of t</span>
  <span id="freeText3003107839245857364" style="display:none"><b>“Activism is not a journey to the corner store, it is a plunge into the unknown. The future is always dark.”</b> Solnit believes in the power of purposeful individuals working towards social justice, even in the face of dispiriting evidence (the largest protests the world had seen didn’t stop the Iraq War). Instead of perfectionism, she advises flexibility and resilience; things could be even worse had we not acted. At first I thought it depressing that 15 years on we’re still dealing with many of the issues she mentions here, and the environmental crisis has only deepened. But her strong and stirring writing is a reminder that, though injustice is always with us, so is everyday heroism. </span>
  <a data-text-id="3003107839245857364" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

